    <parallel-group>3-B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Shares PlaybookOutputHandler.cs switch with tasks 048, 049, 051 — sequential within wave 3-B per task-create Step 3.8 file-overlap auto-demotion rule (CRIT-8 fix)</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add a `FormPrefill` case to `PlaybookOutputHandler.HandleOutputAsync` that is INTENTIONALLY a no-op (no user-visible content emitted; no streaming; no chat). The pre-fill flow (`MatterPreFillService` / `ProjectPreFillService`) is the consumer that produces form-prefill output via its own pipeline; NFR-07 forbids modification of that flow. The handler simply returns gracefully when `NodeDestination = FormPrefill`. Implements spec FR-14d FormPrefill branch.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in NFR-07 pre-fill flow contracts (signature, timeout, `$choices`, `useAiPrefill`).</role>

  <goal>
    `PlaybookOutputHandler.HandleOutputAsync` FormPrefill case explicitly returns without emitting any user-visible content. Comment documents the rationale (NFR-07 forbids handler-side modification; pre-fill flow is consumer). Unit test verifies no SSE event + no chat token emitted. Pre-fill flow regression: `useAiPrefill` hook end-to-end still works (existing test).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-14d FormPrefill branch + design §1.3 ("FormPrefill: no-op in handler — pre-fill flow MatterPreFillService / ProjectPreFillService is consumer; NFR-07 forbids modifying it"). This case exists for switch completeness, not for user-visible behavior. Without it, the switch would either throw or fall through to default — both undesirable.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/PlaybookOutputHandler.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/MatterPreFillService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ProjectPreFillService.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-07: pre-fill flow contracts preserved (signatures, 45s timeout, `useAiPrefill`, `$choices`). Binding constraint.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-14d FormPrefill: handler is no-op; pre-fill flow is consumer.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Handler in `Services/Ai/Chat/`; AI-internal.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Wave 3-B parallel safe — distinct switch arm.</constraint>
  </constraints>

